nodes.bodyText:
I believe every time this is evaluated for a given row, it creates this list and iterates through.  It would be good to avoid additional copies if possible.  I read through the documentation for Arrays.asList and it actually seems to just wrap the array and not copy it, so I think this does just one copy, which is what the original code did.  You might want to verify that, but I think you're good.
I would make sure to add comments here documenting why this combination is necessary!  Otherwise someone will simplify it again and rebreak it.
Consider making a separate static method in CodeGenUtil that's documented well so that it's use stands out.  If all variadic args works fine, it could be something like:
public static <T> List<T> listOf(final T... a) {
    return ImmutableList.copyOf(a);
  }

